4:
You were amazing! I'll... keep doing
my best, too!
6:
I feel all encouraged now! Thank
you, Lap-T! I'll see you at your next
concert!
8:
Your bellybutton was super cute
today, as always! Awesome
tummy... Tummy yummy!
11:
I guess it comes with the territory,
but you've got a lot of weirdo fans.
15:
Nothing wrong with people having
fun their own way! I'm totally cool
with it!
20:
Wow. You're tough in more ways
than one.
25:
It's almost time for iFanFest... So the
fans are getting charged up to
cheer for their oshis.
42:
It's a glorious festival which crowns
the best of the best in new idol
talent! It's a massive commercial
event, too.
50:
Our producers have been
developing new products and
promos for this event.
53: I'm working on a new song for it, too!
58: You write your own music, too?!
62:
Well, you know. It's kinda standard
for a social media idol.
65:
...Oh, but don't tell anyone about
that just yet! I want to make it a
surprise!
69:
Heh. Exactly as I would expect from
a professional idol!
71:
...You're playing to WIN, are you not?
Idol Hero?
76:
Of course! That's all I've got on my
mind, really!
78:
This festival is the gateway to
success for anyone seeking to
become a top idol. I have to win!
82:
Yeah! I'm wanna do whatever I can
to help you win!
89:
Since we're collaborating with her,
we'll change your outfit to match
Laputina's and have you compete
togeth—
93:
I was kidding! Just being a hero is
enough for me!
98: We're already at the finals, eh?
106:
P-please, Lap-T! Make sure you take
the win here! My career's on the line!
109:
Leave it to me! I'll show you the
burning spirit of a true idol hero!
116:
Attention, all attendees. An incident
has occurred in the local area, but
rest assured that the venue is wholly
unaffected—
119:
...A bombing? Of all the times for
something like this to happen...
123:
We'll take care of this. Laputina, just
focus on what you've gotta do for
the competition!
136:
No, wait! You're up next! If you leave
now, I'm done for... Cut it with the
jokes!
139:
Come on, Producer! I'm everyone's
idol hero!
142:
Lap-T! Do you have any idea what
you're doing?! Don't abandon your
dreams!
143:
After all your blood, sweat, and
tears, this is your one chance to
make it big! New idols don't get a
"next time," you know!
145:
I'm going to ask you again, Lap-T.
Are you really ready to throw it all
away?
151:
Exactly... Glad you came around. It's
stupid to abandon everything so
easil—
156:
Even if I leave that dream behind...
I'm sure I'll be all right.
158: Sorry, Producer. I've gotta go now!
165:
I-it's no good! They've got us pinned
down!
168:
Lap-T?! I thought you were at the
festival—
171:
It's okay. I'm here for you. Be brave
and move forward!
174:
Ah... All right! We can do it, guys! Let's
go!
178:
Let's give 'em everything we've got!
Chaaarge!
182:
Are you okay? I know that festival
meant a lot to you...
188:
I was able to keep dreams alive and
help others be courageous. Could
an idol ask for anything more
worthwhile than that?
191:
But I did miss my chance to make it
big... and INOBEC is probably toast,
too.
194:
So I'll just have to find a new way
forward for me!
199:
In that case, PBC would like to
welcome you with open arms!
202:
I'd... love to make such an offer, but I
just don't see that happening.
219:
You're a resilient one, to say the
least. Even when dealt such an
unfortunate hand...
224: You found a new way forward.
234:
Huh? Wait. Look at this video... Looks
like a live broadcast... AH! We're still
connected to the live feed!
238:
That's perfect! I was going to reveal
it at the festival... But let's do it here!
241:
Here's my new song, everyone! This
one's called... Brave Strike!
